Spanning five light-filled, historic shophouses, The Working Capitol on Keong Saik houses companies ranging from startups to multinationals. Productivity, buzz, and community are the words we most often hear used to describe the atmosphere in the space. The Keong Saik Road location's spacious 33,000-square-foot interior includes multiple event spaces for up to 200 people, a beer garden for after-work socialising, and three attached restaurants, ready to host client luncheons and team happy hours.
The Working Capitol was born when co-founders Ben and Saranta Gattie decided to transform an old biscuit factory on Keong Saik Road into a unique coworking and lifestyle destination. Spaces Paya Lebar Quarter provides professionals and creatives with a collaborative environment from which to base themselves. Within the two towers of this inspirational structure, entrepreneurs are presented with a choice of private offices, dynamic meeting rooms and shared working environments, which make growing a business or starting a creative endeavour simple. This is an incredibly accessible location, both with its disabled facilities and elevators, and its close proximity to transport links. What’s more, it enhances the productivity of its tenants with its high-speed Wi-Fi connections, receptive and helpful administrative support staff, and a variety of services ranging from an on-site coffee bar to cloud storage that transfers across Spaces locations.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: Joo Chiat is a conservation area in the east of Singapore known for its multicultural influences and rich history – and Joo Chiat stands at the heart of the action on the area’s main thoroughfare. Within the colourful, traditional shop houses that line the road across from the building, you’ll find a wide selection of eateries, art galleries, design studios, upmarket retail outlets and boutique hotels. And if this impressive local architecture has sparked your interest in local culture, there’s no shortage of attractions in the area. Joo Chiat is an impressive art deco structure with plenty of kerb appeal and with multiple balconies on the second and third floors. Behind this striking façade is a suite of designer private offices, spacious meeting rooms and buzzing communal areas. Plug in to our community of like-minded professionals and watch your business thrive. The roof can also be accessed and used for lazy lunches or networking events. And for ultimate commuter convenience, you’ll find a number of bus stops and subway stations a stone’s throw from the office door.
